ext":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method. Configure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"referenc